2082.subject: KIN
2082.descrlong: Provides information and experiences to assist students reflect upon and make decisions about what constitutes well-being between partners and among families. While highlighting the diversity of structures in relationships, provides information and tools in such areas as communication and conflict resolution, lifespan issues, sexuality, parenting, separation, and wellness. (Offered spring semester).
